50|$|Banks can deposit excess {{liquidity}} overnight with the CNB at {{the discount rate}} and can borrow overnight funds at the lombard rate. Thus these two rates create a corridor for the short-term money market rates. Moreover, the CNB conducts open market operations {{in the form of}} repurchase agreements (REPOs). The basic duration is 2 weeks. Currently the CNB is absorbing {{excess liquidity}}. The aim of these operations is to influence <b>short-term</b> <b>rates</b> which subsequently affect economic activity, the flow of capital, and inflation.|$|E
