50|$|The Public Bank Group is {{well known}} for its strong {{financial}} performance and consistent prudent management. It is consistently accorded with strong credit and financial ratings from local and foreign rating agencies. Public Bank gained a long-term rating of AAA the Rating Agency Malaysia. It is the highest rating accorded by Rating Agency Malaysia. It also received a <b>short-term</b> <b>rating</b> of P1 with stable outlook. Standard & Poor’s reaffirmed Public Bank’s A- long-term <b>rating</b> and A-2 <b>short-term</b> counterparty credit <b>rating</b> with stable outlook. Moody’s Investors Service reaffirmed Public Bank’s foreign currency long-term deposit rating of A3 and <b>short-term</b> deposit <b>rating</b> of P-2 with stable outlook.|$|R
